         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">D'Estaville, [Kew] ¶ 28th June 1873 ¶ My Dear Baron ¶  ¶ Within the last few years a weed has sprung up in the Western District before unknown there, it is usually known there by the named of "Native ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">73.06.28</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Niel Black</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Anthemis cotula</seg> (MEL 718001).</p>
               </note>D'Estaville, [Kew]</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">28th June 1873</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My Dear Baron</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Within the last few years a weed has sprung up in the Western District before unknown there, it is usually known there by the named of "Native Camomile" Its tendency to spread far surpasses any thing I ever saw, It is most pernicious and cannot be destroyed by ploughing, It seems to master any kind of cereal crop, In my opinion it is far more difficult to<seg style="font-weight: bold; "> </seg>get it eradicated than thistle <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I enclose a sample of it and will take it very kind if you will let me know the scientific as also the English name of the plant as I would like to get a Rule introduced in Parliat<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Parliament.</p>
               </note> for its destruction before it overruns the whole Colony <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>If the specimen enclosed hereunto is too small I will be able to send a larger sample in a few days I remain</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">My Dear Baron</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>yours very truly</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Niel Black</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c</p>
         </div>
      </body>
